I"¬<p>While <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/end-to-end-differentiation-enables-powerful-optimization-techniques">training</a> a <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/language-models-are-few-shot-learners">machine learning model</a>, the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/regularization-penalizes-flexibility">training data is fixed</a> and the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/argmin-and-argmax-formalize-optimization">model parameters are changing</a>. In contrast, during <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/few-shot-regime-enables-extreme-customization">inference</a>, the model parameters are fixed and the data itself is changing.</p>
